data.name: gibbonNetR
data.description: R package to use 'torch for R' for automated detection using convolutional neural nets in passive acoustic monitoring (PAM) data

evidence: "gibbonNetR R Package" and installation via `devtools::install_github("https://github.com/DenaJGibbon/gibbonNetR")` indicate an R package authored by named individuals, with no mention of an institution or broader community governance.

"This README provides code for training, testing, and deploying, different convolutional neural network model architectures for automated detection and classification of acoustic data." indicates it is an end-user tool to run analyses, not just a library component in a larger system.
